Welcome to Valves Online - all of your valving needs at the click of your finger

When it comes to control valves, Process Systems has been leading the pack in Australia for more than 30 years. Aimed at providing the best product and the best service at the best price, Process Systems are the number one choice for valves in the country...

Free Shipping Australia Wide

We offer free delivery to all Australian regions and our assistance with any other related requirements

Large range of solenoid valves including direct acting, differential, high pressure, high temperature, explosion proof along with the various body material options available. Applications include solenoid valves for water, steam, chemicals, high pressure...

Comprehensive range of Butterfly Valves for general industrial, mining and agricultural applications. Sizes from 50mm to 2400mm in wafer, lugged and flanged. All are available with manual, electric or pneumatic actuation (double acting or spring...

Ball valve range includes 316 stainless steel, nickel plated brass, UPVC, 2 way, 3 way, threaded, flanged and fire safe. All ball valves are available with pneumatic, electric and manual operation. Well known for their durability and reliability.

Check Valves from 50mm to 3500mm in both Cast Iron and 316 Stainless Steel. Models include swing, piston, ball, pilot and duck bill. Applications include mining, mineral processing, power industries, sewerage, tidal and water treatment.

Process Systems has a range of globe valves (shut-off valves) in both threaded and flanged options. Materials include cast steel from DN 50 (50 mm) to DN 300 (300 mm) and 316 Stainless Steel. Great for controlling steam and other media.

Gate Valves from 50mm to 3500mm. Body materials Ductile Iron, 316 Stainless Steel & Cast Steel with resileant (soft) and metal seat options. Applications include mining, mineral processing, power industries, sewerage and water treatment.
